title: Cortnee Vine Opens Up On Mental Health | 10 News+
description: Matildas star Cortnee Vine sat down with 10 News+ reporter Tara Rushton to open up about her battle with mental health as a professional athlete.  She reflects on everyday Aussies’ reactions to her history-making penalty kick for the Matildas, and the anxiety that followed after reaching such a career high. title: Sydney Man Shot Dead By Police After Six-Hour Siege | 10 News
description: Police have shot a man dead after a six-hour siege on the Central Coast. The man barricaded himself inside his own home during what appears to have been a mental health episode, before attempting to burn and stab an officer. A specialist police team will now investigate their own officers, as a critical incident is declared. title: ICE Agents Kill American Citizen In Minneapolis Triggering Widespread Protests | 10 News
description: There is anger on the streets of the US city of Minneapolis tonight after a federal immigration agent shot a woman dead in her car. President Donald Trump says it was self-defence. title: PM Calls Bondi Royal Commission, Northern Victoria Bushfires, ICE Fatally Shoots Woman | 10 News+
description: Anthony Albanese has caved after weeks of pressure and announced a royal commission into antisemitism, social cohesion, and the circumstances that lead to the Bondi Beach terror attack. Former High Court judge Virginia Bell is at the helm, and the commission will replace the already announced New South Wales state-based inquiry, and incorporate the review run by former spy chief Dennis Richardson, who will deliver his interim report in April. Jenny Roytur, the niece of Bondi victim Boris Tetleroyd, spoke to 10 News+ about her reaction to the Prime Minister’s announcement.  Victoria is facing the most hazardous heatwave conditions since the Black Summer bushfires of 2019-20, with the South-West, Wimmera, Northern Country and North Central regions issued a catastrophic fire danger rating. Residents of up to a dozen towns are being told to evacuate, as a bushfire currently burning in Longwood continues to spread. A second blaze east of Wodonga is also burning out of control.  Queensland’s north-west has been devastated by a deluge of floodwater after weeks of torrential rain. Farmers are bracing for huge losses, with around 30,000 head of livestock estimated to be dead or missing. Local grazier Beau Harrington from Julia Creek’s Brinard Station spoke to 10 News+ about the harrowing experience of dealing with the destruction from the heart of the floods.  America is once again on edge after Renee Good, a US citizen, was shot and killed by an ICE agent in Minneapolis, Minnesota. People have gathered at the site of the shooting to protest and to hold a vigil. The mayor of Minneapolis told ICE to “get the f*ck out” of the city, while US Homeland Security Secretary Kristi Noem defended the shooting, saying Good had tried to run over the officer before he opened fire.
